  769|       |        // We need to gather sym[curr_char][last_char] structs.
  770|       |        // These hold 4 32-bit values, so are 128 bit each, and
  771|       |        // are loaded from 32 distinct addresses.
  772|       |        //
  773|       |        // We load them into 32 128-bit lanes and then combine to get
  774|       |        // 16 avx-256 registers.
  775|       |        // These are now ABCD ABCD ABCD ABCD... orientation
  776|       |        // Code we can then "gather" from these registers via a combination
  777|       |        // of shuffle / permutes / and / or operations.  This is less
  778|       |        // IO than repeating 4 sets of gathers/loads 32-times over.
  779|       |
  780|       |        // DCBA holding 4 elements in a syms[] array
  781|       |        // -> 4-way rotate via shuffles
  782|       |        // [0] DCBA  11 10 01 00  E4
  783|       |        // [1] CBAD  10 01 00 11  93
